// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Adventure hooks
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: adventure_hook
A merchant offers {2d6 * 50} gold to escort a mysterious locked chest across the [@region] — he refuses to say what is inside.
A child in the village of [@village_name] claims to have seen the dead walking in the old graveyard at midnight.
The local lord has vanished; his last known location was the [@location].
Three adventurers set out for the [@location] a week ago — only their weapons have returned, dragged by a frightened mule.
A bounty of {1d4 * 100} gold is posted for the capture — alive — of a fugitive wizard last seen near [@location].
An ancient map surfaces at auction, apparently showing a vault beneath the [@location] filled with pre-empire treasure.
The river that supplies [@village_name] has run black for three days; something upstream is wrong.
A dying courier delivers a sealed letter intended for someone who died years ago — and the contents reference something that cannot yet have happened.
Strange lights have been seen above the [@location] every night for a month; farmers refuse to work their fields.
A beloved temple healer has gone missing; her notes mention a secret ritual she planned to perform alone at the [@location].

