Table: villain_role
a disgraced [|noble|general|high priest|archmage|guild master] seeking revenge
a [|mad|grieving|corrupted|ambitious] [|wizard|warlord|cleric|rogue|noble]
the puppet master behind a [|thieves' guild|death cult|mercenary company|secret society]
an ancient [|vampire|lich|revenant|dragon] posing as a [|merchant|advisor|scholar|noble]
a demonically [|possessed|bound|created|summoned] [|knight|inquisitor|herald|oracle]

Table: villain_motive
to [|raise the dead|open a portal to the Abyss|destroy the old gods|break the wards on the prison plane]
to avenge the [|destruction of their homeland|murder of their family|betrayal by a former ally]
to achieve [|immortality|godhood|absolute power|the annihilation of a hated people]
to fulfil an ancient [|pact|prophecy|oath|curse] at any cost
to reclaim [|a stolen throne|lost magical knowledge|an artefact of immense power]
to bring about a [|new world order|golden age — for their kind only|purge of the weak]

Table: villain_strength
Commands the loyalty of {1d4 + 2} powerful lieutenants.
Possesses an artefact that renders them [|immune to fire|impossible to scry|immune to mind magic|resistant to all weapons].
Has infiltrated the highest levels of [|the city guard|the temple|the merchant council|the king's court].
Knows the true name of a [|demon|dragon|elemental|angel] and can summon it once.
Has already won the first battle — the party starts on the back foot.
Controls the only [|bridge|port|pass|water supply] into the region.

Table: villain_weakness
Bound by an ancient oath that prevents [|lying|harming children|entering sacred ground|acting on the new moon].
Obsessively loyal to one ally who could be turned against them.
Their power source can be disrupted by [|the light of dawn|a specific rune|running water|the sound of bells].
Haunted by genuine guilt; an appeal to conscience may give them pause.
Their lieutenants fear them but do not respect them — a show of weakness could shatter their army.
Relies entirely on a single powerful magical item; destroy it and they are mortal.

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Complications
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: complication
The party is being [|followed|framed|watched|manipulated] by a [|rival adventuring group|shadowy organisation|vengeful NPC|unknown third party].
An NPC the party trusts is [|working for the villain|keeping a dangerous secret|slowly being corrupted|not who they claim to be].
The villain has [|already struck once|taken a hostage the party cares about|sabotaged their supplies|bribed a key ally].
The location is [|structurally unstable|warded against magic|partially flooded|under enemy surveillance].
Time pressure: the ritual / attack / collapse / deadline happens in {1d6} days.
A moral dilemma: the most effective solution would cause serious [|harm to innocents|destruction of something irreplaceable|violation of the law].
Political interference: a [|lord|guild|church|kingdom] with its own agenda is trying to control the outcome.
Environmental hazard: [|plague|famine|wildfire|blizzard|flood] complicates travel and resources.

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// The twist
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: twist
The villain is not the true threat — they are trying to stop something far worse.
The quest giver has been lying: their real motive is [|personal greed|a family secret|revenge|fear of exposure].
One of the party's trusted allies is revealed to be [|a spy|the villain's relative|under a compulsion|not human].
The "artefact" / "prisoner" / "treasure" the party seeks does not exist — it was bait.
The location itself is [|sentient|cursed to repeat a tragedy|a prison for something that must not be released|slowly dying].
Success will cost the party something precious and irreplaceable.
The villain had a point: the people they were fighting for are [|corrupt|guilty|responsible for the villain's suffering].
The final confrontation reveals a connection between the villain and one party member's past.
There is a second villain who has been manipulating both sides from the start.
Destroying the threat would trigger a catastrophe; the solution requires sacrifice, not violence.

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Rewards
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: reward
{1d6 * 100} gold pieces found among the villain's possessions.
\a [|+1|+2|+3] [|sword|axe|bow|shield|staff|dagger|warhammer|rapier] of [|striking|protection|speed|returning|fire|frost|lightning].
A [|spell scroll|ritual book|map|coded letter] that opens a new adventure thread.
The gratitude of [@village_name]: they offer free [|lodging|equipment repairs|healing|horses] for life.
\a rare [|potion of healing|potion of greater healing|potion of flying|potion of invisibility|elixir of health].
A deed to [|a small plot of land|a disused mine|an abandoned building|a share in a merchant vessel].
A favour owed by [|a noble|a guild master|a wizard|a temple elder] — to be called in at a future date.
Knowledge: the villain's documents reveal the location of something [|dangerous|valuable|long-lost].

// ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Side quests
// ----------------------------------------------------------------

Table: side_quest
Locate a missing person — [@village_name] farmer's child, last seen near the [@location].
Recover a [|stolen|cursed|lost|hidden] [|family heirloom|holy relic|magical component|piece of armour] for a grateful NPC.
Investigate rumours of [|disappearances|undead activity|strange lights|unexplained fires] in [@village_name].
Deliver a sealed message to a contact in [@village_name] before a [|rival|pursuer|deadline] can intercept it.
Escort a [|wounded soldier|frightened scholar|disillusioned cultist|refugee family] to safety.
Clear a [|cave system|ruined building|stretch of road|river crossing] of [|bandits|monsters|undead|traps] blocking passage.
Obtain a specific [|rare herb|spell component|piece of information|tool] needed to overcome a challenge in the main quest.
Defuse a conflict between two factions in [@village_name] before it erupts into open violence.
